Circa means "around," which you generally use the middle of a range for (see citations for range).  If Jesus was 33, then He wasn't crucified in 33 AD.  If Jesus was crucified in 33 AD, then He wasn't 33 at the time.  Actually look at the dates *and the sources*.

How is this POV? What other "church" would Jesus's followers have gone on to become? The Church of Scientology? The definition of a "Christian" is someone who believes in and follows (or at least purports to follow) the message and teachings of Jesus. That basically means that anyone who was following Jesus in the first century is a Christian by definition. Furthermore, the original lead said "Christian Church." Please obtain consensus on the talk page before changing it to say anything else.
